To set up a Linux Ubuntu server, you will need the following:

A computer or virtual machine with at least 512 MB of RAM and 10 GB of storage to run the Ubuntu server operating system.

A bootable Ubuntu server ISO image, which can be downloaded from the Ubuntu website.

A method to install the operating system on the computer or virtual machine, such as a USB flash drive or DVD.

Basic knowledge of the Linux command line and system administration.

Once you have all of these components, you can begin the installation process by booting the computer or virtual machine from the Ubuntu server ISO image and following the prompts to install the operating system. After the installation is complete, you will need to perform some basic configuration tasks, such as setting the hostname, creating a user account, and configuring network settings.

It's also recommended to have a good understanding of server security and hardening. Also, best practice to have regular backups and updates.




