Linux Ubuntu server web server nginix va php o'rnatish
To set up a web server on a Linux Ubuntu server using Nginx and PHP, you will need to follow these steps:

Install Nginx:
Copy code
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install nginx
Install PHP and the necessary extensions:
Copy code
sudo apt-get install php-fpm php-mysql
Configure Nginx to use PHP-FPM. You will need to edit the default Nginx configuration file, which is typically located at /etc/nginx/sites-available/default, and make sure it contains the following lines:
Copy code
        location ~ \.php$ {
                include snippets/fastcgi-php.conf;
                fastcgi_pass unix:/var/run/php/php7.2-fpm.sock;
        }
Restart Nginx to apply the changes:
Copy code
sudo systemctl restart nginx
Test PHP by creating a file called "info.php" in the web root directory and put the following code in it:
Copy code
<?php
phpinfo();
?>
Then access it via browser by visiting the server IP or domain name followed by /info.php.

6.You can now place your PHP web application in the web root directory and configure Nginx to serve it.

Please note that these commands are for Ubuntu 18.04, PHP version may vary for different distributions or versions

Also, it is important to keep your server and software up to date with security updates and patches to prevent any vulnerabilities.




